#: src/container/overview.md:1
msgid "Containers — Overview"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:3
msgid ""
"Perry ships a first-class container subsystem that lets a TypeScript program "
"manage OCI containers and multi-container stacks directly, without shelling "
"out to `docker compose` or hand-rolling subprocess wrappers. The user-facing "
"API is split across two TypeScript modules:"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:8
msgid "Module"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:8 src/container/volumes.md:10
msgid "Use case"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:10
msgid "[`perry/container`](./containers.md)"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:10
msgid ""
"Single-container lifecycle: `run`, `create`, `start`, `stop`, `remove`, "
"`inspect`, `logs`, `exec`, plus image management."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:11
msgid "[`perry/compose`](./compose.md)"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:11
msgid ""
"Multi-service orchestration: `up`, `down`, `ps`, `logs`, `exec`, `start`, "
"`stop`, `restart`, `config` — driven by a TS object literal that mirrors the "
"Compose spec."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:13
msgid ""
"Both modules compile to **direct calls into a Rust backend** that talks to "
"whatever OCI-compatible runtime is on the host. There is no JavaScript "
"runtime in the loop, no YAML file emitter, no `docker-compose` shell-out: "
"the spec is a TS object, the engine is in-process, and orchestration logic "
"(dependency ordering, rollback, healthcheck waits) runs natively."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:19
msgid "Backend auto-detection"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:21
msgid ""
"You do **not** configure a runtime up-front. On first use, Perry probes a "
"platform-specific priority list of OCI runtimes (with a 2-second timeout per "
"candidate) and caches the first one that responds:"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:25
msgid "Probe order"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:27
msgid "**macOS / iOS**"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:27
msgid ""
"`apple/container` → `orbstack` → `colima` → `rancher-desktop` → `lima` → "
"`podman` → `nerdctl` → `docker`"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:28 src/container/overview.md:29
msgid "`podman` → `nerdctl` → `docker`"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:31
msgid ""
"The choices reflect three priorities: platform-native runtimes win "
"(`apple/container` on macOS, the others on Linux), daemonless / rootless "
"runtimes (`podman`, `nerdctl`) beat daemon-based ones, and `docker` is "
"always the last fallback."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:36
msgid ""
"The same `ComposeSpec` produces deterministic behavior across every backend "
"in this list — same project-namespaced names, same DNS aliases, same "
"`ContainerInfo` shape from `inspect`, with explicit warnings (or hard "
"failures, opt-in) when a feature like `privileged: true` can't be honored on "
"the chosen runtime. See [Cross-Backend Determinism](./determinism.md) for "
"the architecture."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:43 src/container/containers.md:182
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"import { getBackend, detectBackend } from \"perry/container\";\n"
"\n"
"async function pickBackend(): Promise<void> {\n"
"    // Synchronous: returns the canonical name of the active backend\n"
"    // (`\"docker\"`, `\"podman\"`, `\"apple/container\"`, `\"orbstack\"`,\n"
"    // `\"colima\"`, `\"lima\"`, `\"nerdctl\"`, …). When called before any\n"
"    // async FFI has triggered detection, getBackend() performs a\n"
"    // synchronous in-place probe with the same 2 s timeout per\n"
"    // candidate that detectBackend() uses, so the result is live.\n"
"    console.log(`backend: ${getBackend()}`);\n"
"\n"
"    // Async + verbose: returns a JSON array of every probed backend\n"
"    // with availability + version + reason for unavailable ones. Use\n"
"    // this when you want to surface a \"diagnostics\" panel to the user.\n"
"    const probed = await detectBackend();\n"
"    console.log(probed);\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

