msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:173
msgid ""
"You need fine-grained per-container security knobs (`cap_add`, `seccomp`, "
"`read_only`, `user`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:176
msgid "Reach for **`perry/compose`** when:"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:178
msgid ""
"You're deploying a multi-service application (web + db, app + cache + "
"worker, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:180
msgid "You need dependency-ordered startup with healthcheck conditions."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:181
msgid ""
"You want named volumes, custom networks, and rollback-on-failure semantics."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:183
msgid "You'd otherwise reach for a `docker-compose.yaml` file."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/overview.md:185
msgid ""
"The two modules share a runtime; you can mix them in the same program if you "
"e.g. use `perry/compose` for the long-running stack and `perry/ container` "
"for one-off tasks against the same containers."
