#: src/container/production-patterns.md:3
msgid ""
"This page is a guided tour of "
"[`example-code/forgejo-deployment`](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/tree/main/example-code/forgejo-deployment), "
"a working production-quality deployment of [Forgejo](https://forgejo.org/) "
"(self-hosted Git) using the real Forgejo image from the official "
"`data.forgejo.org` registry. The example was driven end-to-end against live "
"Docker; the patterns here are what survived."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:9
msgid ""
"The full source is at "
"[`example-code/forgejo-deployment/main.ts`](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/tree/main/example-code/forgejo-deployment/main.ts). "
"This page documents the _patterns_, not every line."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:12
msgid "Lifecycle: `up + verify + exit 0` then a separate `--down`"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:14
msgid ""
"Perry's runtime currently does not deliver `process.on('SIGINT', ...)` to "
"your TS code. So the canonical \"Ctrl-C tears down the stack\" pattern isn't "
"writable today. Instead, follow the `docker compose up -d` / `docker compose "
"down` model: deploy + verify + exit 0, with teardown behind a separate "
"`--down` invocation:"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:20
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"async function main() {\n"
"  const args = process.argv.slice(2);\n"
"  const config = buildConfig();\n"
"  if (args.includes(\"--down\")) {\n"
"    await cmdDown(config);\n"
"  } else {\n"
"    await cmdUp(config);\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:32
msgid "The example's `cmdUp`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:34
msgid "Pre-flight backend probe + port-conflict guard."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:35
msgid "Call `up()` with the canonical spec."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:36
msgid ""
"Poll readiness probes (postgres `pg_isready`, then forgejo `/api/healthz`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:38
msgid "Print an operator-facing banner with URLs + \"how to tear down\"."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:39
msgid "Exit 0. Containers keep running thanks to `restart: unless-stopped`."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:42
msgid "The example's `cmdDown`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:44
msgid ""
"Re-call `up()` with the same spec — idempotent: services already running are "
"detected and skipped, returning the same handle the original deploy got."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:47
msgid ""
"Call `down(handle, { volumes: destroy })`. `destroy` is set from "
"`FORGEJO_DESTROY_ON_EXIT=1`."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:50
msgid "Two-network split: internal db + public web"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:52
msgid ""
"The Forgejo example puts postgres on an internal-only network and forgejo on "
"both that network and a public bridge:"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:55
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"networks: {\n"
"  \"forgejo-db-net\":  { driver: \"bridge\", internal: true }, // postgres "
"unreachable from host\n"
"  \"forgejo-web-net\": { driver: \"bridge\" },                 // forgejo's "
"web + SSH ports\n"
"},\n"
"services: {\n"
"  db: {\n"
"    networks: [\"forgejo-db-net\"],\n"
"    // no `ports:` — postgres is invisible to the host\n"
"  },\n"
"  forgejo: {\n"
"    networks: [\"forgejo-db-net\", \"forgejo-web-net\"],\n"
"    ports: [\"3000:3000\", \"2222:22\"],  // public web + SSH\n"
"  },\n"
"},\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:72
msgid ""
"Why: postgres should never be reachable from the host (or from sibling "
"stacks), but forgejo needs both inbound HTTP from the host AND outbound DB "
"queries to postgres. Two networks is the cleanest expression of that split."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:77
msgid "Stable container names for cross-service DNS"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:79
msgid ""
"Perry's compose engine creates each container with a `{md5}-{random}` "
"derived name and doesn't yet register the service KEY (`db`, `forgejo`) as a "
"network alias. So `FORGEJO__database__HOST: 'db:5432'` would fail name "
"resolution at runtime. The Forgejo example pins explicit `container_name` "
"values:"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:85
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"const dbHostname      = \"forgejo-db\";\n"
"const forgejoHostname = \"forgejo-app\";\n"
"\n"
"services: {\n"
"  db: {\n"
"    image: `postgres:${pgVersion}`,\n"
"    container_name: dbHostname,                  // ← stable target\n"
"    // …\n"
"  },\n"
"  forgejo: {\n"
"    image: `data.forgejo.org/forgejo/forgejo:${version}`,\n"
"    container_name: forgejoHostname,\n"
"    environment: {\n"
"      FORGEJO__database__HOST: `${dbHostname}:5432`,  // ← refers to it\n"
"      // …\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
"},\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:106
msgid ""
"See [Networking → Cross-service DNS](./networking.md#cross-service-dns) for "
"the full backstory and why this is the workaround until service-key "
"network-alias support lands."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:110
msgid "OpenSSH on :22 + `START_SSH_SERVER=false`"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:112
msgid ""
"Forgejo's official image runs `/usr/sbin/sshd` on container port 22 in its "
"entrypoint script, then runs the forgejo binary. If you also set "
"`FORGEJO__server__START_SSH_SERVER=true`, forgejo's Go-based built-in SSH "
"server tries to bind :22 too — and the container exit-0's with \"bind: "
"address already in use\"."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:118
msgid ""
"The standard Forgejo deployment pattern is to **let OpenSSH handle SSH on "
":22 and tell forgejo not to start its own**:"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:121
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"environment: {\n"
"  FORGEJO__server__START_SSH_SERVER: \"false\",   // ← critical\n"
"  FORGEJO__server__SSH_PORT:         \"2222\",    // public host port\n"
"  FORGEJO__server__SSH_LISTEN_PORT:  \"22\",      // container-internal "
"port\n"
"  // …\n"
"},\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:130
msgid ""
"Forgejo writes git users' authorized_keys to `/data/git/.ssh/`, which the "
"in-container OpenSSH consumes. Git operations route through sshd on :22, "
"then forgejo's `gitea-shell` script."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:134
msgid "Healthcheck-gated dependency startup"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:136
msgid ""
"postgres takes ~5–10 seconds to initialise on first run (initdb + listener "
"bind). Without gating, forgejo starts immediately, can't connect, and burns "
"retry budget. The fix is a per-service `healthcheck` plus `depends_on: { "
"svc: { condition: 'service_healthy' } }`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:142
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"db: {\n"
"  image: \"postgres:16-alpine\",\n"
"  // …\n"
"  healthcheck: {\n"
"    test: [\"CMD-SHELL\", \"pg_isready -U forgejo -d forgejo\"],\n"
"    interval: \"5s\",\n"
"    timeout: \"3s\",\n"
"    retries: 10,\n"
"    start_period: \"30s\",\n"
"  },\n"
"},\n"
"forgejo: {\n"
"  // …\n"
"  depends_on: { db: { condition: \"service_healthy\" } },\n"
"},\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:160
msgid ""
"Even with that, the example _also_ runs an explicit readiness loop "
"post-`up()` for the full HTTP `/api/healthz` path — the healthcheck gates "
"**container startup** but the operator banner shouldn't print until the API "
"is _serving_:"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:165
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"async function waitForForgejo(stack: number, timeoutMs: number): "
"Promise<boolean> {\n"
"  const deadline = Date.now() + timeoutMs;\n"
"  while (Date.now() < deadline) {\n"
"    try {\n"
"      // Probe from INSIDE the forgejo container so the docker-proxy\n"
"      // bind-up window doesn't trip the host-side curl.\n"
"      await exec(stack, \"forgejo\", [\n"
"        \"wget\", \"-q\", \"-O\", \"/dev/null\",\n"
"        \"--timeout=2\", \"--tries=1\",\n"
"        \"http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/healthz\",\n"
"      ]);\n"
"      return true;\n"
"    } catch (_e) {\n"
"      await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, 2000));\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"  return false;\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:186
msgid ""
"`/api/healthz` is Forgejo's no-auth liveness endpoint that returns 200 once "
"the web server is up AND the database / cache subsystems pinged "
"successfully. Don't use `/api/v1/version` — when `REQUIRE_SIGNIN_VIEW=true` "
"(a production-hardening default) it returns 401, and `wget` exits non-zero "
"on HTTP error responses."
msgstr ""

#: src/container/production-patterns.md:192
