"declare the audio background mode entitlement; foreground playback works out "
"of the box."
msgstr ""

#: src/system/audio_module.md:135
msgid "Web Audio API (`AudioContext` + `AudioBufferSourceNode` + `GainNode`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/system/audio_module.md:136
msgid ""
"miniaudio v0.11.22 (`perry-audio-miniaudio` crate). PulseAudio / PipeWire / "
"ALSA on Linux, WASAPI / DirectSound / WinMM on Windows, AAudio (API 26+) / "
"OpenSL ES on Android — chosen at runtime."
msgstr ""

#: src/system/audio_module.md:138
msgid "Web autoplay policy"
msgstr ""

#: src/system/audio_module.md:140
msgid ""
"Browsers don't allow audio playback before a user gesture. The "
"`AudioContext` is lazily created on the first `loadSound()` / `play()` call; "
"if that call happens **before** any user interaction, the context starts in "
"a suspended state and your `play()` is queued. Trigger a "
"user-interaction-bound `resumeAll()` (or just any other `play()` inside a "
"click handler) to release it."
