msgstr ""

#: src/cli/allowed-hosts.md:40
msgid "Pattern syntax"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/allowed-hosts.md:42
msgid ""
"**Exact host** — `\"api.example.com\"` matches that hostname on any "
"scheme/port/path."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/allowed-hosts.md:44
msgid ""
"**Subdomain wildcard** — `\"*.cdn.example.com\"` matches every direct or "
"transitive subdomain. The bare suffix does NOT match — `*.foo.com` does not "
"match `foo.com`."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/allowed-hosts.md:47
msgid ""
"**URL prefix** — `\"https://api.acme.com/v1/*\"` matches any URL starting "
"with that literal prefix. Path-bound entries only gate path-bearing call "
"sites — `net.connect(\"api.acme.com\")` against a URL-prefix entry does NOT "
"match (use a host-style entry for that)."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/allowed-hosts.md:51
msgid ""
"**Universal** — `\"*\"` matches everything (escape hatch for incremental "
"migration; defeats the static guarantee)."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/allowed-hosts.md:54
msgid "Dynamic URLs / hosts"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/allowed-hosts.md:56
msgid ""
"Non-literal arguments — `fetch(someVar)`, `net.connect(port, hostVar)`, "
"template strings with substitutions — defeat the static `grep`\\-the-binary "
"guarantee. They're refused by default:"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/allowed-hosts.md:60
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"const url = \"https://api.example.com/x\";\n"
"const resp = await fetch(url); // refused unless allowDynamicHosts: true\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/allowed-hosts.md:65
msgid "To allow them, set `perry.allowDynamicHosts: true`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/allowed-hosts.md:71
msgid "\"allowDynamicHosts\""
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/allowed-hosts.md:76
msgid ""
"The code reviewer then has to trust the value of every variable that reaches "
"`fetch(...)` — explicit acknowledgment that the static guarantee is being "
"weakened."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/allowed-hosts.md:80
msgid "Opt-in semantics"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/allowed-hosts.md:82
msgid ""
"If `perry.allowedHosts` is **not set**, the entire pass is disabled and "
"existing builds compile unchanged. The host opts in by setting the array; "
"once set, the gate is strict."
msgstr ""

