"**`--lockdown` (#496)** — gates host code itself against the "
"arbitrary-code-execution surfaces (perry-jsruntime, `perry.nativeLibrary` "
"archives, `child_process.*`). Orthogonal: `perry.permissions` is per-dep, "
"`--lockdown` is whole-binary."
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/capabilities.md:101
msgid ""
"**`allowedHosts` (#502)** — narrows `net:fetch` from \"any URL\" to \"URLs "
"matching this allow-list.\" A dep with `net:fetch` permission still has to "
"clear the egress allow-list at every call site."
